In Daugavpils June 6 shooting attack, police registered 214 witnesses – approximately 60 of whom still need to give testimonies, said Daugavpils Regional State Police Regional Chief Andrejs Sella.

France, Russia, Britain and the United States have offered strong united support for the new German government and its chancellor, Angela Merkel.

In the aftermath of an incident which took place in Daugavpils June 6, a public order affected by alcohol or intoxicants needs to be lessened, as named by officers of the State Police in Latvia.

A data from Eurostat shows that for the year 2013, Latvia and Estonia were in second and third place, as the European Union countries providing the highest number of maximum months provide a country’s maternity benefit in the amount of up to 100% of the paid salary.
